27/01/2003
DAVOS, Switzerland -- Greek Foreign Minister George Papandreou said Sunday (26 January) Europe could still contribute to the peace process in Iraq.
Papandreou met with US Secretary of State Colin Powell in an attempt to discuss alternatives to military intervention.
Powell stressed that both sides of the Atlantic need to find some compromise and leave behind the critical remarks exchanged by US and European officials over the past few days.
Papandreou also met with Turkish Prime Minister Abdullah Gul and ruling party leader Recep Tayyip Erdogan, to discuss Iraq, Cyprus and issues related to Turkey's EU bid.
(Kathimerini - 27/01/03;
Athens News Agency, Macedonian Press Agency, Anadolu Agency - 26/01/03)
